The draw for the Beach Soccer Africa Cup of Nations 2022 will be conducted on Friday, 24 June 2022 in Maputo, Mozambique. The draw will kick off at 10:00 local time (08:00 GMT) and live-streamed on CAF digital Platforms. Title holders Senegal, who hosted the 2021 edition in Saly Portudal, are amongst the 14 teams engaged in this qualifying phase.   WAFU B U17: Golden Eaglets  through to  2023 AFCON     Police raid Napoli, Lille over Osimhen’s deal     Eaglets‘ll be ready for final, says Ugbade   The Beach Soccer Africa Cup of Nations Mozambique 2022 will be held from 21 to 30 October 2022. The seven qualified teams will join 2021 runners-up Mozambique who qualify automatically as hosts. Teams to feature in the draw include Cameroon, Comoros, Cote D’Ivoire, Egypt, Ghana, Libya, Madagascar, Malawi, Morocco, Nigeria, Senegal, Seychelles, Tanzania and Uganda.